arguments.prompt:
You are implementing a Blazor Web App shipment tracker for a logistics company. The project is already scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-ee8647bd13c04f99a264c22c0bf847ad/ShipmentTracker/` with:
- Solution: `ShipmentTracker.sln`
- Server project: `ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker/`
- Client project: `ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.Client/`
- Mode: Interactive Auto, Global with Individual auth
- Database: SQLite via EF Core (already configured in `Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs`)

## Requirements
1. Dispatchers view a list of shipments with status and destination
2. Customers check their shipment status and estimated delivery
3. Every page has interactive controls
4. Auth with individual accounts (already scaffolded)

## Architecture (Auto mode rules)
- All interactive components MUST go in the `.Client` project
- Data access via HTTP APIs only (components can't use DbContext directly)
- Define service interfaces in `.Client`, implement with HttpClient there, and with direct DB access on server
- Register matching services in both Program.cs files

## Implementation Plan

### 1. Shared Models — Create in `.Client` project (so both projects can reference them)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/Shipment.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime ShippedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public DateTime? ActualDelivery { get; set; }
    public string RecipientName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string? CustomerEmail { get; set; }
    public string? Notes { get; set; }
}

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Delayed,
    Returned
}
```

### 2. Service Interface — in `.Client` project

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync();
    Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task<Shipment> CreateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment);
    Task<Shipment> UpdateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment);
    Task DeleteShipmentAsync(int id);
}
```

### 3. Client-side implementation (HttpClient)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentHttpService.cs`:
```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentHttpService(HttpClient http) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
        => await http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<Shipment>>("api/shipments") ?? [];

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        var response = await http.GetAsync($"api/shipments/track/{trackingNumber}");
        if (!response.IsSuccessStatusCode) return null;
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment> CreateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment)
    {
        var response = await http.PostAsJsonAsync("api/shipments", shipment);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return (await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>())!;
    }

    public async Task<Shipment> UpdateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment)
    {
        var response = await http.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{shipment.Id}", shipment);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return (await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>())!;
    }

    public async Task DeleteShipmentAsync(int id)
    {
        var response = await http.DeleteAsync($"api/shipments/{id}");
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
    }
}
```

### 4. Server-side — Add Shipment entity to DbContext

Edit `ShipmentTracker/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` to add:
```csharp
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
// Add DbSet<Shipment> Shipments property
```

### 5. Server-side service implementation

Create `ShipmentTracker/Services/ShipmentDbService.cs`:
```csharp
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Data;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Services;

public class ShipmentDbService(ApplicationDbContext db) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
        => await db.Shipments.OrderByDescending(s => s.ShippedDate).ToListAsync();

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
        => await db.Shipments.FirstOrDefaultAsync(s => s.TrackingNumber == trackingNumber);

    public async Task<Shipment> CreateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment)
    {
        db.Shipments.Add(shipment);
        await db.SaveChangesAsync();
        return shipment;
    }

    public async Task<Shipment> UpdateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment)
    {
        db.Shipments.Update(shipment);
        await db.SaveChangesAsync();
        return shipment;
    }

    public async Task DeleteShipmentAsync(int id)
    {
        var shipment = await db.Shipments.FindAsync(id);
        if (shipment is not null)
        {
            db.Shipments.Remove(shipment);
            await db.SaveChangesAsync();
        }
    }
}
```

### 6. API Endpoints — Create `ShipmentTracker/ShipmentEndpoints.cs`:
```csharp
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

namespace ShipmentTracker;

public static class ShipmentEndpoints
{
    public static void MapShipmentEndpoints(this WebApplication app)
    {
        var group = app.MapGroup("api/shipments").RequireAuthorization();

        group.MapGet("/", async (IShipmentService service) =>
            Results.Ok(await service.GetAllShipmentsAsync()));

        group.MapGet("/track/{trackingNumber}", async (string trackingNumber, IShipmentService service) =>
        {
            var shipment = await service.GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(trackingNumber);
            return shipment is null ? Results.NotFound() : Results.Ok(shipment);
        }).AllowAnonymous(); // Customers can track without auth

        group.MapPost("/", async (Shipment shipment, IShipmentService service) =>
            Results.Created($"/api/shipments/track/{shipment.TrackingNumber}", await service.CreateShipmentAsync(shipment)));

        group.MapPut("/{id}", async (int id, Shipment shipment, IShipmentService service) =>
        {
            shipment.Id = id;
            return Results.Ok(await service.UpdateShipmentAsync(shipment));
        });

        group.MapDelete("/{id}", async (int id, IShipmentService service) =>
        {
            await service.DeleteShipmentAsync(id);
            return Results.NoContent();
        });
    }
}
```

### 7. Pages in `.Client` project

**Remove** `Counter.razor` and `Weather.razor` from `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/`.

**Update `Home.razor`** to be a welcome/landing page.

**Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/Shipments.razor`** — Dispatcher page showing all shipments with filtering:
```razor
@page "/shipments"
@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models
@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization
@attribute [Authorize]
@inject IShipmentService ShipmentService

<PageTitle>Shipments</PageTitle>

<h1>Shipment Dashboard</h1>

<div class="mb-3 row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Filter by destination..." @bind="filterText" @bind:event="oninput" />
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <select class="form-select" @bind="statusFilter">
            <option value="">All Statuses</option>
            @foreach (var status in Enum.GetValues<ShipmentStatus>())
            {
                <option value="@status">@status</option>
            }
        </select>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <button class="btn btn-primary" @onclick="ShowCreateForm">+ New Shipment</button>
    </div>
</div>

@if (showCreateForm)
{
    <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5>Create New Shipment</h5>
            <EditForm Model="newShipment" OnValidSubmit="CreateShipment" FormName="CreateShipment">
                <div class="row g-2">
                    <div class="col-md-3">
                        <input class="form-control" placeholder="Tracking #" @bind-value="newShipment.TrackingNumber" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-2">
                        <input class="form-control" placeholder="Origin" @bind-value="newShipment.Origin" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-2">
                        <input class="form-control" placeholder="Destination" @bind-value="newShipment.Destination" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-2">
                        <input class="form-control" placeholder="Recipient" @bind-value="newShipment.RecipientName" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-2">
                        <input class="form-control" placeholder="Customer Email" @bind-value="newShipment.CustomerEmail" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-1">
                        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-success">Save</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </EditForm>
        </div>
    </div>
}

@if (shipments is null)
{
    <p><em>Loading shipments...</em></p>
}
else
{
    <table class="table table-striped table-hover">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Tracking #</th>
                <th>Origin</th>
                <th>Destination</th>
                <th>Status</th>
                <th>Shipped</th>
                <th>Est. Delivery</th>
                <th>Recipient</th>
